lic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png" width="1200" height="269.5054945054945" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:327,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:1200,&quot;bytes&quot;:104524,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://thesilkroadnexus.substack.com/i/196014553?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:&quot;center&quot;,&quot;offset&quot;:false}" class="sizing-large" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!_IS1!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61e527fb-75b4-4eb1-acda-ef904a8e051f_2572x578.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><h2>The Capex Question: $200B and the Free Cash Flow Cliff</h2><p>This is the number that spooked the market in February and continues to dominate the narrative. Amazon spent $44.2 billion in cash capital expenditures in Q1 alone. Trailing twelve-month free cash flow collapsed to $1.2 billion, down 95% year over year. The $200 billion full-year capex guidance implies spending that exceeds Shopify&#8217;s entire market capitalization.</p><p>But the composition matters. The vast majority of this capex is going into AWS infrastructure: data centers, custom silicon (Graviton, Trainium, Nitro), and networking equipment. The commerce side of the business is not the primary capital consumer. Amazon&#8217;s new large-format fulfillment centers use next-generation robotics that actually reduce per-unit fulfillment cost. The commerce business is getting more capital-efficient while AWS gets more capital-intensive.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-img" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!vTCt!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08843267-7b58-40e5-8064-85d73b5862de_2568x882.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!vTCt!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F08843267-7b58-40e5-8064-85d73b5862de_2568x882.pn