_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa39d94ed-9a68-4a04-abeb-aee36bc76637_708x462.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!pOYb!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa39d94ed-9a68-4a04-abeb-aee36bc76637_708x462.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset"><button tabindex="0" type="button" class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image"><svg role="img" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="var(--color-fg-primary)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><g><title></title><path d="M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex="0" type="button" class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The commerce and supply chain angle nobody is discussing: SpaceX&#8217;s Starlink has over 10,000 satellites and 9 million users. By volume, Amazon is far behind. But Amazon has something SpaceX does not: AWS. Jassy wrote explicitly that Leo will integrate seamlessly with AWS to enable enterprises and governments to move data back and forth for storage, analytics, and AI. This is not an internet service. This is a cloud on-ramp. Connectivity becomes a wedge into enterprise compute, and compute becomes the margin layer. Musk sells internet. Amazon is selling infrastructure. For commerce operators, the implication is direct: satellite-enabled logistics networks, real-time supply chain visibility in rural and remote geographies, and edge computing for last-mile optimization become possible at a scale that does not exist today.</p><div class="embedded-publication-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:4464661,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;THE SILK ROAD NEXUS&quot;,&quot;logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!PE2u!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d01b369-18f8-426d-a6b8-d16966c0c114_600x600.png&quot;,&quot;base_url&quot;:&quot;https://thesilkroadnexus.substack.com&quot;,&quot;hero_text&quot;:&quot;The strategies, trade-offs, and logistics tech defining the next decade of commerce. Written by a Senior Product Leader in Commerce. The only newsletter analyzing the unit economics of the physical world. Free, high-signal, and respects your inbox&quot;,&quot;author_name&quot;:&quot;Nikhil Varshney&quot;,&quot;show_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;logo_bg_color&quot;:&quot;#ffffff&quot;,&quot;language&quot;:&quot;en&quot;}" data-component-name="EmbeddedPublicationToDOMWithSubscribe"><div class="embedded-publication show-subscribe"><a class="embedded-publication-link-part" native="true" href="https://thesilkroadnexus.substack.com?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_campaign=publication_embed&amp;utm_medium=web"><img class="embedded-publication-logo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!PE2u!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d01b369-18f8-426d-a6b8-d16966c0c114_600x600.png" width="56" height="56" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span class="embedded-publication-name">THE SILK ROAD NEXUS</span><div class="embedded-publication-hero-text">The strategies, trade-offs, and logistics tech defining the next decade of commerce. Written by a Senior Product Leader in Commerce. The only newsletter analyzing the unit economics of the physical world. Free, high-signal, and respects your inbox</div><div class="embedded-publication-author-name">By Nikhil Varshney</div></a><form class="embedded-publication-subscribe" method="GET" action="https://thesilkroadnexus.substack.com/subscribe?"><input type="hidden" name="source" value="publication-embed"><input type="hidden" name="autoSubmit" value="true"><input type="email" class="email-input" name="email" placeholder="Type your email..."><input type="submit" class="button primary" value="Subscribe"></form></div></div><h3>SECTION 4</h3><p><strong>The Full Stack Play: Amazon Owns Every Layer of the AI Value Chain</strong></p><p>The most discussed section of the letter is AI. But the commerce and supply chain implications are underappreciated. Jassy laid out what I call Amazon&#8217;s Full Stack Play. Amazon now owns virtually every layer of the AI technology stack, and each layer feeds the others.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-img" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!If3w!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1afe8e7f-a76d-4df5-be90-67e3a7975c98_1200x1200.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!If3w!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1afe8e7f-a76d-4df5-be90-67e3a7975c98_1200x1200.png 42